To showcase a detailed explanation and computation of the Pythagorean theorem on an HTML page, you can use mathematical symbols and diagrams. Here is an example of how you can do this:
1. Use an HTML editor to create a new page or open an existing one.
2. Create a section for your explanation and computation of the Pythagorean theorem. You can use headings, paragraphs, and lists to organize your content.
